What you need to know:  The Sh100 million one-stop border post launched two years ago is expected to ease trade and free movement of goods between Kenya and Uganda upon completionThe project is among Sh5 billion projects funded by the African Development Bank (AfDB) set to open up the East Africa region, including the 45km Kitale-Suam border highwayMr Natembeya said the project is critical for the upgrade of local businesses, with most traders having moved to neighbouring Uganda